    <note>Li(2) Chang [971] His ancestors were Longxi jun Li(2). They avoided the late Tang rebellions by fleeing south to Jiangnan and Hunan with the "power elite of the four regions" (sifang haojie) and "capital bureaucratic lineages" (jingdu shizu). Di(1) Zundu's  [7067] and Wei(5) Yan's [7390] son-in-law (twice: sororate), Huang(2) Shuao's [856] father-in-law. Qin Guan, WJ, Hou, 'xia,' v8b; XCB, 371.19b, 376.3b, 377.2b, 384.4a, 398.6b-7a, 399.13a, 403.20a, 406.13b, 407.6a, 414.8a, 438.1a; XCBSB, 5.21b; SHY:ZG, 44.36b-37a; SHY:SH, 49.22a; SS, 344.5b; Su Song, WJ, 55.17a-23a. CBD, 2, 869-70.See Huang(2) Tingjian's [7111] funerary inscription for his sister's daughter's husband, Song(2) Ban [15402]. CBD, 2, 916.</note>
